<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 3:00PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Scotland,
southeastern Richmond and southern Hoke Counties through 345 PM
EDT...
At 259 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles north of Auburn to near Mccoll to near
Elrod. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Raeford, Hamlet, Maxton, Antioch, Wagram, Gibson, East
Laurinburg, Silver City and Laurel Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
